<div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">

    <p n="1-2">
        1827,<note>The era is not specified and this millesime is not followed, as one would expect, by a symbol for year (unless, what is read as "7" is this symbol in an unstandard form, as are unstandard forms the symbols for <foreign>mācam</foreign> and <foreign>tēti</foreign> in line 2). In the present context (colonial La Réunion, antiquity of the Māriyammaṉ temple), it appears that date is in the common era and not in the Śaka era (as one would expect in a inscription from Tamil Nadu itself).</note> month of Cittirai, date 7.
    </p>
    
    <p n="2-6">
        Māriyammaṉ temple constructed <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaṭṭappaṭṭatu</foreign></supplied> by<note>See phrase in instrumental case (-<foreign>ālē</foreign>), which precedes <foreign>kaṭṭappaṭṭatu</foreign>. Because of the illegible portions of lines 4-5, it is not clear whether <foreign>kaṭṭappaṭṭatu</foreign> is to be construed with a subject in nominative case (the donor) and an agent in intrumental case (the contractor) or with just an agent in intrumental case (the donor alone).</note> <gap reason="lost"/> Vēṅkaṭa Reṭṭiyar <gap reason="lost"/> Matān <gap reason="lost"/>.
    </p>
	
</div>
    
    <div type="translation" xml:lang="fra" resp="part:emfr">

    <p n="1-2">
        1827, mois de Cittirai, date 7.
    </p>
    
    <p n="2-6">
        Temple de Māriyammaṉ construit par <gap reason="lost"/> Vēṅkaṭa Reṭṭiyar <gap reason="lost"/> Matān <gap reason="lost"/>.
    </p>
	
</div>

